import random = It's used to import the random function
type = this check the type of data you're using
eg
name = "James"
print(type(name))

f-string
print (f"My name is {James}")

the modulo % : It gives you the remainder of a division. eg. 7 % 2 = 1


random.choice = it's use to get random words or letters from the given list or variables
random.shuffle = this shuffle a list of items
.title() = it capitalize the 1st word of the sentence.